How to read it

If ER_VISITS_WITH_PROC_MATCH ≈ ER_VISITS → ✅ join key is correct and present.

If lots are “without match” → then claim id mismatch or missing procedures.

✅ Query B (show sample rows where they match)

This gives you a human-readable sample:

SELECT TOP 50
    ev.CLAIM_ID_ER,
    fcp.CLAIM_ID,
    fcp.SERVICE_FROM_DATE,
    fcp.CODE,
    fcp.CODE_NAME
FROM BI_ANALYSIS.dbo.FACT_ER_VISITS ev
JOIN BI_ANALYSIS.dbo.FACT_CLAIM_PROCEDURE fcp
    ON fcp.CLAIM_ID = ev.CLAIM_ID_ER
WHERE ev.ER_STATUS = 'TRUE ER'
ORDER BY ev.ER_DATE DESC;

You will see CLAIM_ID_ER and CLAIM_ID equal in the output.

