That’s totally plausible.

One more “sanity” query I recommend

This tells you how many ER visits you have total:

SELECT
  COUNT(*) AS ER_VISITS,
  COUNT(DISTINCT CLAIM_ID_ER) AS DISTINCT_ER_CLAIMS
FROM BI_ANALYSIS.dbo.FACT_ER_VISITS
WHERE ER_STATUS = 'TRUE ER'; -- 422763
422763 
BOTH ARE SAME

Usually these will be the same (since each ER visit row has one CLAIM_ID_ER).

